 as Brunswick. The placename is from the genitive case of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Bruno</i> (borne by the Duke of Saxony who founded the city in 861) + Old Saxon <i>wīk</i> ‘dwelling place’, ‘settlement’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gräfin von Braunschweig was born about 1004, in Germany, her father, Graf Brun I. von Braunschweig, was 36 and her mother, Gisela von Schwaben Kaiserin des Heiligen Römischen Reiches, was 15. She had at least 2 sons with Thiemo I. von Formbach."},"et":{"um 1004–":"umbes 1004–Surnud","1003–1038":"1003–1038","1004–Female":"1004–Surnud","0980–1049":"0980–1049","1018–1040":"1018–1040","1024–1059":"1024–1059","0970–1016":"0970–1016","0990–1043":"0990–1043","1043":"1043","1040":"1040","1018":"1018","1016":"1016","1049":"1049","1038":"1038","0970":"0970","1059":"1059","1004":"1004","Abt 1024":"umbes 1024","1003":"1003","0990":"0990","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","um 1004":"umbes 1004","um 1003":"umbes 1003","um 1018":"umbes 1018","Schweinachgau, Germany":"Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"um 1004–":"noin 1004–Kuollut","1003–1038":"1003–1038","1004–Female":"1004–Kuollut","0980–1049":"0980–1049","1018–1040":"1018–1040","1024–1059":"1024–1059","0970–1016":"0970–1016","0990–1043":"0990–1043","1043":"1043","1040":"1040","1018":"1018","1016":"1016","1049":"1049","1038":"1038","0970":"0970","1059":"1059","1004":"1004","Abt 1024":"noin 1024","1003":"1003","0990":"0990","1024":"1024","0980":"0980","um 1004":"noin 1004","um 1003":"noin 1003","um 1018":"noin 1018","Schweinachgau, Germany":"Saksa","Germany":"Saksa"},"fr":{"um 1004–":"environ 1004–Décédée","1003–1038":"1003–1038","1004–Female":"1004–Décédée","0980–1049":"0980–1049","1018–1040":"1018–1040","1024–1059":"1024–1059","0970–1016":"0970–1016","0990–1043":"0990–1043","1043":"1043","1040":"1040","1018":"1018","1016":"1016","1049":"1049","1038":"1038","0970":"0970","1059":"1059","1004":"1004","Abt 1024":"environ 1024","1003":"1003","0990":"0990","1024":"1024","0980":"0980",